The Heroku Boilerplate includes all the files you need to get NodeJS set up on Heroku. The files were created from the Heroku tutorial, "Getting Started with Node.js on Heroku/Cedar" http://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/node-js

Follow along with the tutorial and use the files included to get your Heroku Node project up and running easily.

run the following commands:

npm install -d
heroku apps:create --stack cedar <app_name_here>
heroku addons:add mongolab:starter # free 240mg mongo tier